The new checksum for an updated task is calculated but is not persisted back to storage. The `updatedTask.checksum` is assigned *after* `this.storage.update` has already completed. The returned object has the correct checksum, but any subsequent `getTask()` call will retrieve the task from storage with the old, incorrect checksum, which could lead to data integrity issues.

The checksum should be calculated based on the merged state of the task and included in the object passed to `this.storage.update`.

```typescript
  async updateTask(
    taskId: string, 
    updates: Partial<PersistedTask>, 
    expectedVersion?: number
  ): Promise<PersistedTask> {
    const existingTask = await this.storage.get(taskId);
    if (!existingTask) {
      throw new Error(`Task ${taskId} not found`);
    }

    const version = expectedVersion ?? existingTask.version;

    // Add history entry if state is changing
    if (updates.status && updates.status.state !== existingTask.status.state) {
      const historyEntry: TaskHistoryEntry = {
        timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),
        previousState: existingTask.status.state,
        newState: updates.status.state,
        reason: updates.status.message
      };

      updates.history = [...(existingTask.history || []), historyEntry];
    }

    if (this.config.enableChecksums) {
      const mergedTask = { ...existingTask, ...updates };
      updates.checksum = this.calculateChecksum(mergedTask);
    }

    return await this.storage.update(taskId, updates, version);
  }
```

