If `connection.sendRequest` throws an error, the connection is not released back to the pool, and `processQueue()` is not called. This can lead to a connection leak (the connection remains in an `ERROR` state) and can starve requests waiting in the queue.

```suggestion
    try {
      const result = await connection.sendRequest(method, params);
      await this.releaseConnection(connection);
      return result;
    } catch (error) {
      if (this.config.enableMetrics) {
        this.metrics.failedRequests++;
      }
      // On error, remove the faulty connection from the pool.
      await this.removeConnection(agentUrl, connection);
      // Ensure the queue is processed to prevent starvation.
      await this.processQueue();
      throw error;
    }
```

