The comments for `protected` and `signature` should be more specific about the encoding. According to [RFC 7515 (JWS)](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc7515#section-2), these values are **Base64url-encoded**, not just "base64-encoded". Using the correct term is important for implementers to avoid ambiguity and potential encoding/decoding errors. The example signature in `docs/specification.md` correctly uses Base64url encoding.

```
  // The protected JWS header for the signature. This is a Base64url-encoded
  // JSON object, as per RFC 7515. Required.
  string protected = 1 [(google.api.field_behavior) = REQUIRED];
  // The computed signature, Base64url-encoded. Required.
  string signature = 2 [(google.api.field_behavior) = REQUIRED];
```

